<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><song><title>Psalm 23 (Salmo 23)</title>
<lyrics>[V1]
 The Lord is my shepherd, I've everything I need
 He lets me rest in fields of grass
 And leads me to quiet fresh waters
 He gives me new strength
 He guides me in the right paths
 As He has promised, the Lord

[V2]
 Even if I go
 Through the deepest darkness Lord
 I will not be afraid
 For You are with me
 Your shepherd's rod and staff will protect me
 Your shepherd's rod and staff will protect me

[V3]
 You prepare a banquet for me
 Where all my enemies can see me
 You welcome me as an honoured guest
 And fill my cup to the brim
 I know that your goodness and love
 Will be with me all my life
 And your house will be my home
 As long as I shall live</lyrics>
<author>Karen Marra</author>
<hymn_number>697</hymn_number>
</song>